  "texts": [
    "Thus, A(s x) = 0 means that x is equally likely to be implicitly framed as either human or non-human (P HUM = P OBJ), and A = 1 implies that the entity is e 1 ≈ 2.7 times more likely to be implicitly framed as human than as non-human in the context of sentence s.",
    "Implementation Details Following the approach of Antoniak et al. (2023), whose method we build upon for measuring semantic representations, we use the spaCy dependency parser to split texts into sentences and parse semantic triples (subject, verb, and object) from the texts.",
